Ansaldo, AS Roma, Eni: Italian Equity Market Preview for Feb. 16

-- B y   A l e s s a n d r a   M i g l i a c c i o
-- 
2011-02-16T05:00:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/ansaldo-as-roma-eni-italian-equity-market-preview-for-feb-16.html
The following companies may be
active in Italian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close.  Italy’s benchmark FTSE MIB Index fell 186.53, or 0.8
percent, to 22,823.82 in Milan.  Ansaldo SpA (STS IM):  Finmeccanica SpA ’s (FNC IM) railway
technology unit said it won a 200 million euro ($270 million)
contract for a technological upgrade of the railway between the
cities of Turin and Padua. The shares were unchanged at 10.9
euros.    AS Roma SpA  (ASR IM): One of the Italian soccer club’s
owners, Compagnia Italpetroli SpA, said a group of U.S.
investors led by Thomas DiBenedetto will have 30 days to hold
exclusive talks aimed at acquiring the team. The shares lost 0.5
percent to 1.16 euros.    Eni SpA  (ENI IM): Russia’s OAO Gazprom Neft will sign an
agreement to enter the Italian oil company’s Elephant oil
project in Libya, Russia President Dimitry Medvedev’s foreign
policy aide Sergei Prikhodko told reporters in Moscow before
talks between Medvedev and Italian Prime Minister  Silvio Berlusconi . Eni’s stock rose 0.7 percent to 18.4 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
